<P>Playing time: 66'</P>

<P>Recording date: January 1991</P>

<p>Excerpts:<br>
[22], [26] <a href="era91777.htm">Erato 4509-91777-2</a> Music and
Memory - Musiques et M&eacute;moires
</p>

<P>This recording is also the soundtrack for a remarkable video
production of the Roman de Fauvel manuscript, which is well worth
seeing.  (The facsimile, alas, only includes some of the folios in
full color, and thus it is a treat to see everything in color.)</P>

<address>Nathan Wilkes</address>

<hr>

<p>The Roman de Fauvel was one of history's first &quot;multimedia&quot;
productions, combining colorful artwork, poetry and abstract musical
works into one carefully produced book in 1316.  The text was based
on a manuscript by Gervais de Bus which began circulating around
Paris in 1310.  It is a strongly satirical work, and one of the
artistic monuments of the late Middle Ages.</p>

<p>This recording does include a large amount of spoken text
sprinkled in between items.  A couple of classic renditions:</p>

<dl>
<dt>Roman de Fauvel</dt>
<dd>Studio der Fr&uuml;hen Musik - Thomas Binkley<br>
<i><a href="emi30103.htm">EMI Reflexe 63430</a></i></dd>
<dt>Le Roman de Fauvel</dt>
<dd>Clemencic Consort - Ren&eacute; Clemencic<br>
<i><a href="hmu1-994.htm">Harmonia Mundi musique d'abord
190994</a></i></dd>
</dl>

<p>Some people see Philippe de Vitry (c.1291-1361), the attributed
author of the somewhat ephemeral Ars Nova treatise and one of the
composers represented in the Fauvel edition, as the driving force
behind the multimedia compilation as a whole.  A superb recording
devoted specifically to de Vitry:</p>

<dl>
<dt>Philippe de Vitry: Motets and Chansons</dt>
<dd>Sequentia<br>
<i><a href="dhm77095.htm">Deutsche Harmonia Mundi 77095</a></i></dd>
</dl>

<p>A couple of related programs:</p>

<dl>
<dt>Musique vocale du XIVe si&egrave;cle</dt>
<dd>Machaut, Vitry, Fauvel, Anonymous<br>
Mora Vocis<br>
<i><a href="man4946.htm">Mandala 4946</a></i></dd>
<dt>Heu fortuna</dt>
<dd>Musique au temps de Philippe IV le Bel (1260-1314)<br>
La rota<br>
<i><a href="atm22561.htm">Atma 2 2561</a></i></dd>
</dl>

